# Blackjack Game 🃏

A terminal based Blackjack card game built with Python where 
the player competes against the computer.

## How it Works
- Player and computer both get 2 cards at the start
- Player can choose to get more cards or stop
- Cards are randomly selected from a standard deck
- Ace (11) automatically changes to 1 if score goes over 21
- First to reach 21 with 2 cards wins with a Blackjack!

## Game Rules
- Score over 21 = You lose (Bust)
- Blackjack = 21 with exactly 2 cards (instant win)
- Highest score without going over 21 wins
- If both scores are equal = Draw

## Features
- Random card selection
- Automatic Ace handling (11 becomes 1)
- Score calculation system
- Player vs Computer gameplay

## Libraries Used
- random (built-in Python library)

## How to Run
- Make sure Python is installed on your computer
- Download the blackjack.py file
- Open terminal and run: python blackjack.py

